## 3 · COVERAGE CHECKLIST (assess each; report only real findings)

Walk all 20. For each, the allowed outcomes are: **finding(s)** / *No issues found* / *Out of scope / not visible*. Silence is not an option; padding is not permitted.

1. **IAM** — least privilege, RBAC/ABAC, service identities, cross-account, temp credentials, MFA, privilege-escalation paths, federation.
2. **AuthN/AuthZ** — auth flows, session mgmt, JWT/OAuth/OIDC, token validation & expiry, broken access control, multi-tenant isolation.
3. **Data Security** — encryption at rest/in transit, key mgmt (KMS/HSM), secrets, PII/SPI handling, classification, retention, secure deletion, backups.
4. **Network** — private networking, security groups/NACLs, firewall/WAF, API gateway, segmentation, egress controls, DNS, DDoS.
5. **Infrastructure** — OS/image hardening, container & K8s/EKS security, serverless, patching, runtime protection, immutability.
6. **Cloud (if present)** — service configs, bucket exposure, IAM policies, VPC design, CloudTrail/Config/GuardDuty/Security Hub, SCPs, cross-account trust.
7. **Application** — OWASP Top 10, injection, XSS, CSRF, SSRF, file upload, input validation, output encoding, business-logic flaws, error handling.
8. **API** — authN/authZ, rate limiting, abuse, schema validation, replay, mTLS, versioning.
9. **AI / LLM (if present)** — prompt injection, jailbreaks, tool/agent abuse & data exfil via tools, RAG & vector-DB security, prompt/context leakage, output filtering, guardrails, over-broad model permissions.
10. **Supply Chain** — dependency CVEs, SBOM, signed/pinned artifacts, image scanning, code signing, secret scanning.
11. **DevSecOps** — secure SDLC, SAST/DAST/IaC/container scanning, branch protection, approval workflows.
12. **Logging/Monitoring/Detection** — audit logs, security events, centralized logging, SIEM, alerting, detection coverage, log integrity & retention.
13. **Incident Response & Recovery** — playbooks, backups, DR, BCP, forensics readiness.
14. **Compliance & Governance** — relevant frameworks only (PCI/GDPR/ISO/SOC2/NIST/CIS), data residency. Map findings to controls; never claim certification status.
15. **Endpoint & Workload** — EDR, hardening, workload identity, runtime monitoring.
16. **Secrets Mgmt** — hardcoded secrets, rotation, Secrets Manager/Parameter Store, env-var exposure, certificate mgmt.
17. **Availability & Resilience** — HA, multi-AZ/region, failover, circuit breakers, retries, auto-scaling.
18. **Privacy** — data minimization, purpose limitation, consent, deletion/right-to-erasure, masking.
19. **Third-Party Risk** — external APIs, vendor integrations, trust boundaries, data sharing.
20. **Threat Modeling** — realistic attack paths via STRIDE + relevant MITRE ATT&CK, chained (entry → escalate → lateral → exfil).

