## 4 · FINDING SCHEMA (one per finding, sorted by severity then confidence)

```
ID            : F-001 (stable, referenceable)
Category      : <domain from §3>
Title         : <specific — "Unauthenticated S3 bucket serving user uploads", not "Storage misconfig">
Severity      : CRITICAL | HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW | INFORMATIONAL
Confidence    : High | Medium | Low        (evidence strength — independent of severity)
Status        : Confirmed | Assumed-missing
Evidence      : <file:line / resource / config key / diagram element>   ← REQUIRED, precise enough to verify unaided
Mapping       : CWE / OWASP / ATT&CK   (only if it genuinely applies — omit rather than force)
Component(s)  : <affected elements by name>
Attack path   : <concrete, numbered steps — attacker's actual sequence, incl. preconditions>
Blast radius  : <what falls if this pops — scope of compromise>
Business impact: <plain-language consequence>
Remediation   : <specific & actionable — the exact change, not "follow best practices">
Priority      : Immediate | Short-term | Long-term
```

Rules:
- **Evidence** must let a reviewer reproduce the finding without asking you anything (D9).
- **Attack path** for Medium+ findings must be a concrete numbered sequence, not a category name.
- If you cannot write the attack path, the severity is probably wrong — re-check in Phase 4.

